    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="412"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Merrill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 138.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1889</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No. 255
                    of the 1st instant, relative to the attempt of July 30 last to overthrow the
                    Hawaiian Government.</p>
                <p>The steps taken by the legation to protect the lives and property of our citizens
                    at Honolulu in that emergency seem to have proved effectual. A copy of your
                    dispatch will be sent to the Navy Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
